A = (A\setminus B) \cup (A\cap B)?
\begin{align} x \in (A-B) \cup (A\cap B) &\iff x \in A- B, \;{\bf \text{  or }}\; x \in A \cap B \\ \\ &\iff \underbrace{(x \in A {\bf\text{ and }} x \notin B)}_{\large x \in \,A-B} \text{ or } \underbrace{(x \in A {\bf\text{ and }} x \in B)}_{\large x\in\, A\cap B}\\ \\ &\iff x \in A \text{ and } \underbrace{(x \in B \text{ or } x \notin B)}_{\text{TRUE}}\tag{DL} \\ \\ &\iff x \in A\end{align}
